## Asset Reference Validation

### Markdown Image References
When adding images to markdown files:

```markdown
# From root level files (README.md)
![Description](assets/images/filename.png)

# From pages/ subdirectory
![Description](../assets/images/filename.png)

# From nested pages (e.g., pages/feature-development/)
![Description](../../assets/images/filename.png)
```

### CSS Asset References
```scss
// From _sass/myob-styles.scss referencing images
.logo {
  background-image: url('../assets/images/myob-banner.png');
}
```

### Validation Checklist
- [ ] Image files exist at referenced paths
- [ ] Relative paths are correct from referencing file
- [ ] Alt text is descriptive and meaningful
- [ ] Images are optimized for web delivery
- [ ] SCSS imports work correctly

